post_text:
A few announcements:
1. We will begin clearing out student lockers soon. Those bags will be sorted and available for pickup the week of May 18, with specific days and times TBD based on safety guidelines. We will also collect textbooks, library books, music and athletic items at that time.
2. At this time, there is no set plan for graduation that was originally set for May 22. Senior officers and school administration will continue to discuss and consider options. Rest assured that we aim to have a meaningful and safe graduation ceremony for the Class of 2020! RDP!!

post_text:
Blood Drive 352 will be held Tuesday, October 22nd in the West Lafayette Jr.-Sr. High School commons from 2:30pm-7:00pm. Walk ins are welcome, but scheduling in advance will greatly reduce wait times for everyone. You can email me to schedule an appointment or you can register yourself at : https://donate.indiana.versiti.org/…/…/drive_schedule/132425

We are currently 34 units short of our 100 unit a year collection goal so we desperately need your help. We currently have 4 donors signed up to donate so please help spread the word and consider donating. My daughter Caroline received 352 blood transfusions during her 505 day battle with leukemia so I know the importance of every single donation.

All donors must show photo ID and 16 year olds must have a signed parental waiver. We will have pizza, Insomnia Cookies, snacks, drinks, and cards for free t-shirts.

https://www.jconline.com/story/news/2018/05/15/west-lafayette-blood-drive-has-10th-anniversary/612249002/

post_text: Congrats to Arjun Ramani, who was recently named one of the 2017 Indiana Academic All-Stars! Arjun was selected from a field of 266 outstanding nominees from the state’s private and public accredited schools! Academic All-Star distinction recognizes seniors who excel in the classroom first and foremost, but who also are actively involved in their schools and communities, and take on leadership roles in those activities. Arjun will be recognized at a luncheon today at the Indiana Roof Ballroom in downtown Indianapolis. To learn more about the Indiana Academic All-Stars Program, visit http://www.iasp.org/dsp/allstars/.

Beginning Friday, September 18th, visitor parking will be located on Leslie Street in the newly marked "Visitor" spots.

Visitors will still enter through Door 2.

Students returning to school or arriving to school, after the day has commenced, will need to enter Door 2 via the sidewalk that connects to Leslie Street.

If parked in the lower parking lot, or being dropped off, students are asked to use the sidewalk around the back of the building, then along Leslie Street to Door 2.

Thank you for your patience as we make improvements to our parking situation.

post_text: Thank you SIA Foundation! WLHS band directors Mr. Pettit and Mr. Henady accepted an $8,000 grant from the Subaru-Izuzu Foundation to be used for the West Lafayette Band Program. This grant will be used to purchase a trailer in order transport equipment and instruments needed for the Sound Of West Side Marching Band. This trailer will transport all items to and from events including instruments, uniforms, and props for the shows and the She Devils Dance Team.
